1. Project Introduction and Problem Statement¶

IMDB dataset having 50K movie reviews for natural language processing or Text analytics. This is a dataset for binary sentiment classification containing substantially more data than previous benchmark datasets. We provide a set of 25,000 highly polar movie reviews for training and 25,000 for testing. For more dataset information, please go through the following link, http://ai.stanford.edu/~amaas/data/sentiment/

Problem Statement: The objective is to build robust machine learning model using Classification algorithms or Deep Learning algorithm with an aim to detect different types of emotion contained in a collection of English sentences or a large paragraph and accurately predict the overall emotion of the paragraph

def stopwords_stemming(text):
    global stop
    custom_stopwords = ['br', 'like']
    stop = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    stop.update(custom_stopwords)
    text_tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    ## removing stopwords
    tokens_without_sw = [word for word in text_tokens if not word in stop]
    ## stemming
    lemmatizer=WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens_with_stemming = []
    for word in tokens_without_sw:
        word = lemmatizer.lemmatize(word)
        tokens_with_stemming.append(word)
    filtered_sentence = (" ").join(tokens_with_stemming)
    return filtered_sentence


def cleaning_text(text):
    mentions = r'@[A-Za-z0-9]+'
    url_https = 'https?://[A-Za-z0-9./]+'
    url_www = r'www.[^ ]+'
    negations = {"isn't":"is not", "aren't":"are not", "wasn't":"was not", "weren't":"were not",
                 "haven't":"have not","hasn't":"has not","hadn't":"had not","won't":"will not",
                 "wouldn't":"would not", "don't":"do not", "doesn't":"does not","didn't":"did not",
                 "can't":"can not","couldn't":"could not","shouldn't":"should not","mightn't":"might not",
                 "mustn't":"must not"
                }
    
    text = html.unescape(text)
    text = re.sub(mentions, '', text)
    text = re.sub(url_https, '', text)
    text = re.sub(url_www, '', text)
    text = text.lower()
    for a, b in negations.items():
        if a in text:
            text = text.replace(a,b)
    #Removing characters except letters
    text = re.sub("[^a-zA-Z]", " ", text)
    #Removing unnecessary white spaces and stop words using tokenizer
    text = stopwords_stemming(text)
    return text


main_data['text'] = main_data['text'].apply(lambda x: cleaning_text(x))

def logistic_regression():

def ann():
    def build_classifier(optimizer):
        classifier = Sequential()
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 16, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'relu', input_dim = local_X_train.shape[1]))
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 16, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'relu'))
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 1, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'sigmoid'))
        classifier.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
        return classifier

    classifier = KerasClassifier(build_fn = build_classifier)
    parameters = {'batch_size': [100, 300, 500, 700],
                  'epochs': [5, 10, 15, 20],
                  'optimizer': ['adam']}
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator = classifier,
                               param_grid = parameters,
                               scoring = 'accuracy',
                               cv = ShuffleSplit(test_size=0.20, n_splits=1, random_state=42)
                               )

    grid_search = grid_search.fit(local_X_train.toarray(), y_train.values)
    best_parameters = grid_search.best_params_
    best_accuracy = grid_search.best_score_
    cv_results = grid_search.cv_results_
    cv_results = pd.DataFrame(cv_results)

    ## visualizing cv cv_results
    ann_fig = px.scatter(cv_results, x="param_batch_size", y="mean_test_score", color="param_epochs",
                 hover_data=['params'], title="Cross Validation Results for ANN",
            width=600, height=600,
            labels={ # replaces default labels by column name
                "param_batch_size": "Batch Size",  "mean_test_score": "Accuracy", "param_epochs": "Epochs"
            }, template="simple_white")
    ann_fig.show()

    ## training ann with the best parameters
    classifier = build_classifier(best_parameters['optimizer'])
    history = classifier.fit(local_X_train.toarray(), y_train.values, batch_size = best_parameters['batch_size'], epochs = best_parameters['epochs'])

    # Predicting the Test set results
    predictions = classifier.predict(local_X_test.toarray())
    predictions = (predictions > 0.5) ### if >0.5 then 1 otherwise 0
    print(classification_report(y_test.values, predictions))
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.values, predictions)
    print (f"\nAccuracy is {accuracy}")

    return classifier

4.2.8. TF-IDF + Artificial Neural Network¶

In [54]:
def ann():
    def build_classifier(optimizer):
        classifier = Sequential()
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 16, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'relu', input_dim = local_X_train.shape[1]))
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 16, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'relu'))
        classifier.add(Dense(units = 1, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation = 'sigmoid'))
        classifier.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
        return classifier

    classifier = KerasClassifier(build_fn = build_classifier)
    parameters = {'batch_size': [100, 300, 500, 700],
                  'epochs': [5, 10, 15, 20],
                  'optimizer': ['adam']}
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator = classifier,
                               param_grid = parameters,
                               scoring = 'accuracy',
                               cv = ShuffleSplit(test_size=0.20, n_splits=1, random_state=42)
                               )

    grid_search = grid_search.fit(local_X_train.toarray(), y_train.values)
    best_parameters = grid_search.best_params_
    best_accuracy = grid_search.best_score_
    cv_results = grid_search.cv_results_
    cv_results = pd.DataFrame(cv_results)

    ## visualizing cv cv_results
    global ann2_fig
    ann2_fig = px.scatter(cv_results, x="param_batch_size", y="mean_test_score", color="param_epochs",
                 hover_data=['params'], title="Cross Validation Results for ANN",
            width=600, height=600,
            labels={ # replaces default labels by column name
                "param_batch_size": "Batch Size",  "mean_test_score": "Accuracy", "param_epochs": "Epochs"
            }, template="simple_white")
    ann2_fig.show()

    ## training ann with the best parameters
    classifier = build_classifier(best_parameters['optimizer'])
    history = classifier.fit(local_X_train.toarray(), y_train.values, batch_size = best_parameters['batch_size'], epochs = best_parameters['epochs'])

    # Predicting the Test set results
    predictions = classifier.predict(local_X_test.toarray())
    predictions = (predictions > 0.5) ### if >0.5 then 1 otherwise 0
    print(classification_report(y_test.values, predictions))
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.values, predictions)
    print (f"\nAccuracy is {accuracy}")

    return classifier

4.2.9. Word Indexing + Convolutional Neural Network¶

def cnn():

    # vectorize the text samples into a 2D integer tensor
    max_features = 10000 ##vocab size
    tokenizer = Tokenizer(nb_words=max_features)
    tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X)
    sequences_train = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
    sequences_test = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
    # Padding the data samples to a maximum review length in words
    max_words = 450
    local_X_train = sequence.pad_sequences(sequences_train, maxlen=max_words)
    local_X_test = sequence.pad_sequences(sequences_test, maxlen=max_words)

    def build_classifier(optimizer):
        # Building the CNN Model
        classifier = Sequential()      # initilaizing the Sequential nature for CNN model
        # Adding the embedding layer which will take in maximum of 450 words as input and provide a 32 dimensional output of those words which belong in the top_words dictionary
        classifier.add(Embedding(max_features, 32, input_length=max_words))
        classifier.add(Conv1D(32, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'))
        classifier.add(MaxPooling1D())
        classifier.add(Flatten())
        classifier.add(Dense(250, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation='relu'))
        classifier.add(Dense(1, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation='sigmoid'))
        classifier.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
        return classifier

    classifier = KerasClassifier(build_fn = build_classifier)
    parameters = {'batch_size': [100, 300, 500, 700],
                  'epochs': [5, 10, 15, 20],
                  'optimizer': ['adam']}
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator = classifier,
                               param_grid = parameters,
                               scoring = 'accuracy',
                               cv = ShuffleSplit(test_size=0.20, n_splits=1, random_state=42)
                               )

    grid_search = grid_search.fit(local_X_train, y_train.values)
    best_parameters = grid_search.best_params_
    best_accuracy = grid_search.best_score_
    cv_results = grid_search.cv_results_
    cv_results = pd.DataFrame(cv_results)

    ## visualizing cv cv_results
    cnn_fig = px.scatter(cv_results, x="param_batch_size", y="mean_test_score", color="param_epochs",
                 hover_data=['params'], title="Cross Validation Results for CNN",
            width=600, height=600,
            labels={ # replaces default labels by column name
                "param_batch_size": "Batch Size",  "mean_test_score": "Accuracy", "param_epochs": "Epochs"
            }, template="simple_white")
    cnn_fig.show()

    ## training cnn with the best parameters
    classifier = build_classifier(best_parameters['optimizer'])
    history = classifier.fit(local_X_train, y_train.values, batch_size = best_parameters['batch_size'], epochs = best_parameters['epochs'])

    # Predicting the Test set results
    predictions = classifier.predict(local_X_test)
    predictions = (predictions > 0.5) ### if >0.5 then 1 otherwise 0
    print(classification_report(y_test.values, predictions))
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.values, predictions)
    print (f"\nAccuracy is {accuracy}")

    return classifier, tokenizer

def rnn():
    # vectorize the text samples into a 2D integer tensor
    max_features = 10000 ##vocab size
    tokenizer = Tokenizer(nb_words=max_features)
    tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X)
    sequences_train = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
    sequences_test = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
    # Padding the data samples to a maximum review length in words
    max_words = 450
    local_X_train = sequence.pad_sequences(sequences_train, maxlen=max_words)
    local_X_test = sequence.pad_sequences(sequences_test, maxlen=max_words)

    def build_classifier(optimizer):
        # Building the CNN Model
        classifier = Sequential()      # initilaizing the Sequential nature for CNN model
        # Adding the embedding layer which will take in maximum of 450 words as input and provide a 32 dimensional output of those words which belong in the top_words dictionary
        classifier.add(Embedding(max_features, 32, input_length=max_words))
        classifier.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(32)))
        classifier.add(Dense(250, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation='relu'))
        classifier.add(Dense(1, kernel_initializer = 'uniform', activation='sigmoid'))
        classifier.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
        return classifier

    classifier = KerasClassifier(build_fn = build_classifier)
    parameters = {'batch_size': [100, 300, 500, 700],
                  'epochs': [5, 10, 15, 20],
                  'optimizer': ['adam']}
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator = classifier,
                               param_grid = parameters,
                               scoring = 'accuracy',
                               cv = ShuffleSplit(test_size=0.20, n_splits=1, random_state=42)
                               )

    grid_search = grid_search.fit(local_X_train, y_train.values)
    best_parameters = grid_search.best_params_
    best_accuracy = grid_search.best_score_
    cv_results = grid_search.cv_results_
    cv_results = pd.DataFrame(cv_results)

    ## visualizing cv cv_results
    rnn_fig = px.scatter(cv_results, x="param_batch_size", y="mean_test_score", color="param_epochs",
                 hover_data=['params'], title="Cross Validation Results for RNN",
            width=600, height=600,
            labels={ # replaces default labels by column name
                "param_batch_size": "Batch Size",  "mean_test_score": "Accuracy", "param_epochs": "Epochs"
            }, template="simple_white")
    rnn_fig.show()

    ## training cnn with the best parameters
    classifier = build_classifier(best_parameters['optimizer'])
    history = classifier.fit(local_X_train, y_train.values, batch_size = best_parameters['batch_size'], epochs = best_parameters['epochs'])

    # Predicting the Test set results
    predictions = classifier.predict(local_X_test)
    predictions = (predictions > 0.5) ### if >0.5 then 1 otherwise 0
    print(classification_report(y_test.values, predictions))
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.values, predictions)
    print (f"\nAccuracy is {accuracy}")

    return classifier, tokenizer
